posts.cooked:
image 3024×4032 2.75 MB I was trying to deploy code to our chassis for drive testing and when I did, I got ERROR 2[CAN SPARK MAX] IDs:6,8, timed out while waiting for Periodic Status 2 and ERROR 4[CAN SPARK MAX]IDs:2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,WPILib or External HAL Error:Unknown error status. I tried changing the CAN IDs but it didn’t work. Is the driver station not recognizing the CAN IDs or something. I should note that I am using the MAXSwerve Java Template. Link to my code: Mohamadou247/RookieRobot (github.com) May anyone see where the issue is? Thanks in advance.

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: If you connect the USB-C cable to one of the REV devices (SparkMax, PDH, etc) and open the REV Hardware Client, do all expected devices show up in the list?  If not, you have a break in your CAN wiring somewhere (either a disconnect/bad crimp/etc, or an inversion (green->yellow, yellow->green))
When I plug in USB-C to a Spark MAX from my computer, only that specific Spark Max shows up on my REV Hardware client.

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
Is it the same for others as well, or only that one?

Are they connected to the RoboRio over CAN or over PWM?
It is the same for others for the first question. The second question I will have to check tomorrow since I’m not sure off the top of my head.
For the second question, they are connected to the RIO through CAN.

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: Okay.  When you were connected via usb-c, was the robot powered? You should be able to see everything on the CAN bus when connected to any of them, as long as they all have power.
Yes now I am able see every spark max and the pdh.

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: Okay good! Do you still have the errors in the driver station console?
My team is testing it out either today or tomorrow. I will let you know soon. Thanks for your help.

Sorry for not getting back to you. My team was able to test it yesterday and we found out the motors had multiple Active and Sticky faults. We fixed those faults and the issue has been fixed. The motors were able to work.
I have same problem, can you tell how to fix it?
